  "prompt": "How many supercomputers are there in iit kharagpur?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, the Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur (IIT Kharagpur) is equipped with advanced computing resources to support its extensive research and academic activities. While specific details about the exact number of supercomputers at IIT Kharagpur may not be publicly disclosed, the institute typically maintains high-performance computing (HPC) facilities that may include one or more powerful supercomputers or large-scale computing clusters.\n\nThese HPC facilities are utilized across various departments for tasks such as:\n\n- **Scientific Simulations:** Modeling complex physical, chemical, and biological systems.\n- **Data Analysis:** Handling large datasets in fields like bioinformatics, engineering, and environmental science.\n- **Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning:** Training and deploying advanced algorithms and models.\n- **Engineering Design:** Assisting in the computational aspects of engineering projects and research.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding IIT Kharagpur's supercomputing resources, I recommend visiting the official [IIT Kharagpur website](https://www.iitkgp.ac.in/) or contacting their [Center for Information Technology](https://cistp.iitkgp.ac.in/) or relevant departmental offices directly. They can provide detailed insights into the current infrastructure, available computing resources, and any recent upgrades or expansions to their HPC capabilities.",
